-- Australia shares seen opening higher; retail, trade balance data eyed
-- 
-- Wed Apr 02, 2014 05:42PM EDT
-- None



SYDNEY, April 3 (Reuters) - Australian shares are set to open higher on Thursday as Wall Street rose overnight and the S&P 500 index closed at another record high, but investors may exercise caution ahead of key retail and trade balance data due out later in the day.

* Local share price index futures <YAPcm1> rose 0.3 percent, a 13.7-point premium to the underlying S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO> close. The benchmark rose 0.3 percent on Wednesday.  * New Zealand's benchmark NZX 50 index <.NZ50> slipped 0.1 percent in early trade. * The S&P 500 closed at another record high on Wednesday as signs of steady private-sector hiring suggested that the economy was slowly building momentum after a winter-related pullback. * Copper rose to its highest in more than three weeks after a powerful earthquake off the coast of top miner Chile triggered a tsunami alert, raising concerns about supply. Gold rose about 1 percent, its largest gain in three weeks on bargain hunting. * The Australian Competition and Consumer Commision gives its final decision on whether Transurban Group <TCL.AX>'s A$5 billion purchase of state-owned Queensland Motorways should go ahead. * Freelancer Ltd <FLN.AX> said it has acquired virtual content marketplace Fantero.com. [ID:nWNBS00EJE] * National Australia Bank Ltd <NAB.AX> said it has appointed Andrew Thorburn as group chief executive officer and managing director, effective from Aug. 1. Cameron Clyne advised that he will retire as group CEO and managing director of the bank. [ID:nWNBS00EJC] * Retail sales and trade balance data will be released at 0030 GMT.  ------------------ MARKET SNAPSHOT @ 2126 GMT ------------------ INSTRUMENT   LAST   PCT CHG   NET CHG S&P 500 <.SPX>   1,890.90 0.29 5.380 USD/JPY <JPY=>   103.85  0 0.000 10-YR US TSY YLD<US10YT=RR>  2.8027 -- 0.044 SPOT GOLD   <XAU=>   1,289.14 0.7910.140 US CRUDE<CLc1>   99.62   -0.12-0.120 DOW JONES   <.DJI>   16,573.000.24 40.39 ASIA ADRS   <.BKAS>  144.34   0.42  0.60 ---------------------------------------------------------------- * S&P 500 ends at fresh record; data puts jobs in focus   [.N]  * Brent crude loses over $1 as Libya port deal nears [O/R]  * Gold up 1 pct, most in 3 wks, ahead of U.S. jobs data [GOL/]  * Copper hits more than 3-wk high after Chi